<subSubSection pageId="86" pageNumber="87" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="86.[199,1437,1937,1997]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,331,1937,1961]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named in reference to the fimbriate lateral margins of the pronotum and anterior angles of the elytra. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1972,1997]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" reason="1">Distribution.</emphasis>
Currently known only from 
<collectingRegion box="[674,822,1973,1997]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[834,902,1973,1997]" name="Brazil" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[918,1016,1973,1997]" captionStart="FIGURE 126" captionStartId="86.[151,250,1870,1893]" captionTargetBox="[283,1304,337,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-105@86.[283,1304,337,1849]" captionTargetPageId="86" captionText="FIGURE 126. Geographical distributions of Epimetopus species." pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Fig. 126</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
